This is a python3 fork of Richard Penman's Browser Cookie.

What does it do? Loads cookies used by your web browser into a cookiejar
object.

Why is it useful? This means you can use python to download and get the
same content you see in the web browser without needing to login.

Which browsers are supported? Chrome, Firefox, LibreWolf, Opera, Opera
GX, Edge, Chromium, Brave, Vivaldi, and Safari.

How are the cookies stored? All currently-supported browsers store
cookies in a sqlite database in your home directory.
